Grammy award-winning musician, Damini Ogulu, popularly known as Burna Boy, has hit yet another record after his concert sold out in 17, 000 capacity hall in Amsterdam.



Burna boy made history as the first African to sell out the Ziggi Dome in Amsterdam, Netherlands during his concert “Burna Boy Space Drift tour”. This made the management of the facility present a special plaque artwork to celebrate his success.



The text on the plaque read, “The First African to do it.”

